WEBVTT

00:01.914 --> 00:04.047
[upbeat music]

00:04.091 --> 00:05.527
RUDDY: Jack,
what are you doing here?

00:05.570 --> 00:08.051
JACK: Have you met our editor?
Aram Avakian, Al Ruddy.

00:08.095 --> 00:09.313
Did you see
"The Miracle Worker"?

00:09.357 --> 00:10.706
No, missed it.Aram cut it.

00:10.749 --> 00:12.447
It's beautiful work.Thank you, thank you.

00:12.490 --> 00:14.666
Al's gonna need a miracle
to bring us in on budget.

00:14.710 --> 00:16.494
♪

00:16.538 --> 00:17.930
What do you think?

00:17.974 --> 00:19.323
He could have shot it tight
and been done by now.

00:19.367 --> 00:20.411
And what's
with all the presents?

00:20.455 --> 00:22.152
Makes him look
even smaller than he is.

00:22.196 --> 00:24.024
That is no leading man.

00:24.067 --> 00:27.331
I'm just a little nervous,
you know?

00:27.375 --> 00:29.159
So what are we
gonna do about it?

00:29.203 --> 00:31.683
BOB: The producer of my movie
just shook hands

00:31.727 --> 00:33.337
with a goddamn mobster on TV.

00:33.381 --> 00:34.860
I gotta get to New York.

00:34.904 --> 00:36.862
We are going to Texas,
remember?

00:36.906 --> 00:38.690
My movie?I'll meet you there later.

00:38.734 --> 00:40.692
ALI: I'll hold my breath
waiting on that promise.

00:40.736 --> 00:43.217
COLOMBO: Gallo's an animal.
It's unforgivable what he did.

00:43.260 --> 00:45.045
How you doing, Joe?

00:45.088 --> 00:46.002
COLOMBO:
He blew Carmine's head off

00:46.046 --> 00:46.959
with a sawed-off shotgun.

00:47.003 --> 00:48.352
[gunshot]

00:48.396 --> 00:49.571
If he had done this
to a member of your family,

00:49.614 --> 00:51.051
what would you do,
you'd talk to him?

00:51.094 --> 00:52.443
I want your word.

00:52.487 --> 00:55.533
You will not take
any action at this time.

00:55.577 --> 00:56.621
You have my word.

00:56.665 --> 00:58.058
♪

00:58.101 --> 01:01.974
[gunshots]

01:02.018 --> 01:03.802
[tires screeching]

01:06.762 --> 01:09.721
[soft music]

01:09.765 --> 01:16.772
♪

02:31.194 --> 02:34.110
[tense music]

02:34.154 --> 02:41.291
♪

02:49.865 --> 02:51.736
What the fuck is that?

02:51.780 --> 02:54.435
My thoughts precisely.
This is garbage.

02:54.478 --> 02:57.177
This is a mock-up.
The real one will be different.

02:57.220 --> 02:59.004
How so? Less real?

02:59.048 --> 03:00.528
Francis, I promise,

03:00.571 --> 03:01.616
on the day,
it will look better.

03:01.659 --> 03:03.400
Let's put an apple
in its mouth.

03:03.444 --> 03:05.315
I'm not going
to put this crap on screen.

03:05.359 --> 03:07.230
Yes, you will have
to use some lighting

03:07.274 --> 03:08.231
and shadows to--

03:08.275 --> 03:09.493
I'm concerned now, Dean,

03:09.537 --> 03:11.016
that you think
that this is acceptable.

03:11.060 --> 03:12.322
You don't need
to be concerned--

03:12.366 --> 03:13.454
Okay, guys, just relax.

03:13.497 --> 03:15.064
We're all
on the same team here.

03:15.673 --> 03:17.458
You know,
it doesn't feel that way.

03:17.501 --> 03:19.373
RUDDY: Hey, Francis, cool it.

03:19.416 --> 03:22.071
I will cut this scene before
I put this crap on screen.

03:22.114 --> 03:23.551
I'm not cutting the scene.

03:23.594 --> 03:25.683
I'm not cutting the scene!

03:26.728 --> 03:28.947
[sighs]I mean, he's not wrong, Al.

03:28.991 --> 03:31.211
It does look pretty fake.

03:31.254 --> 03:34.126
I need someone I trust
to find me a better one.

03:34.170 --> 03:35.519
Find me a better one.

03:35.563 --> 03:37.434
Me? What?

03:37.478 --> 03:38.740
I'm in charge
of the horse head?

03:38.783 --> 03:39.784
Fuck.

03:39.828 --> 03:40.655
This requires somebody

03:40.698 --> 03:42.222
with great taste and ability.

03:42.265 --> 03:43.875
[scoffs] Wow.

03:43.919 --> 03:47.139
If you blow any more smoke,
my hair might catch on fire.

03:47.183 --> 03:48.880
Aren't you the girl
who met with Joe Colombo

03:48.924 --> 03:50.099
at his social club?

03:50.142 --> 03:52.362
Wasn't exactly
a social call, was it?

03:54.059 --> 03:55.409
[scoffs]

03:55.452 --> 03:57.367
I should've let you stay fired.

03:57.411 --> 04:00.327
[film reel clicking]

04:00.370 --> 04:02.372
Stop!

04:02.416 --> 04:04.592
This is boring.
Why am I watching this?

04:06.985 --> 04:09.988
Pacino is ruining this movie.

04:10.032 --> 04:11.425
I mean, look, he can barely see

04:11.468 --> 04:12.556
over the presents
he's carrying.

04:12.600 --> 04:14.254
He's supposed to be a war hero.

04:14.297 --> 04:15.733
Don't look like any hero
I've ever seen.

04:15.777 --> 04:17.561
The character's supposed
to be intimidating.

04:17.605 --> 04:19.259
Mm, what would you
know about that, Barry?

04:19.302 --> 04:20.869
He's gonna be the Don.

04:20.912 --> 04:24.089
People kissing his ring,
people scared of him.

04:24.133 --> 04:26.744
You scared of him?

04:26.788 --> 04:28.180
We need to fix this

04:28.224 --> 04:29.747
while we still can.

04:29.791 --> 04:32.141
Our stock just rebounded,
but it's not gonna take much

04:32.184 --> 04:33.751
for the board
to change their minds

04:33.795 --> 04:36.276
about keeping Paramount
in our portfolio.

04:36.319 --> 04:38.147
What are you still doing here?

04:38.190 --> 04:40.628
Get your ass
back to set and fix it.

04:40.671 --> 04:43.195
Find me a Michael Corleone
who can deliver.

04:43.239 --> 04:44.327
Jack has your blessing?

04:44.371 --> 04:45.807
Blessing?

04:45.850 --> 04:47.809
If you let this film fail,
I'll rip out your hearts

04:47.852 --> 04:49.506
and show them to you
before you fucking die.

04:49.550 --> 04:51.769
Now get the fuck outta here!

04:53.684 --> 04:58.689
♪

04:58.733 --> 05:03.085
[engine droning]

05:03.128 --> 05:10.092
♪

05:42.516 --> 05:44.387
There is nothing quite like

05:44.431 --> 05:46.998
the intoxicating
authenticity...

05:47.042 --> 05:48.478
[inhales deeply]

05:48.522 --> 05:50.001
Of being on location.

05:50.045 --> 05:52.134
[chuckles] Bob.

05:52.177 --> 05:54.658
What are you doing here?

05:54.702 --> 05:57.008
Well, that's not
the greeting I was expecting.

05:57.052 --> 05:58.880
I'm sorry, you just...

05:59.576 --> 06:01.186
You surprised me.

06:01.230 --> 06:03.145
That's the idea, sweetheart.

06:07.802 --> 06:09.717
Is there somebody in there?

06:12.546 --> 06:16.376
Ali, who's in there with you?Stop.

06:16.419 --> 06:18.334
It's McQueen, isn't it?

06:18.378 --> 06:19.857
You're fucking the Blob.

06:19.901 --> 06:20.902
Please just go.

06:20.945 --> 06:23.034
You asked me
never to leave you.

06:23.078 --> 06:24.558
Do you remember that?

06:24.601 --> 06:25.994
Well, I kept my promise.

06:26.037 --> 06:28.126
You left me a long time ago.

06:28.170 --> 06:30.477
I haven't even heard
from you in over two weeks.

06:30.520 --> 06:32.435
Don't kid yourself.

06:32.479 --> 06:34.219
I've just become something
for you to check off

06:34.263 --> 06:35.960
on your to-do list.

06:36.004 --> 06:37.571
You give everything
to this business,

06:37.614 --> 06:39.747
and there's nothing left
for me.

06:42.271 --> 06:44.404
I'm just getting
out of your way.

06:45.317 --> 06:48.233
[somber music]

06:48.277 --> 06:55.415
♪

07:30.319 --> 07:32.190
[engine revs]

07:47.641 --> 07:49.164
So where is he?

07:49.207 --> 07:50.600
LENNY: Nobody's seen him, boss.

07:50.644 --> 07:52.210
CAESAR:
Gallo's gone underground.

07:52.254 --> 07:53.473
I think he got the message.

07:53.516 --> 07:56.258
Don't underestimate
that crazy bastard.

07:56.301 --> 07:57.999
I heard from some
of Gambino's guys

07:58.042 --> 07:59.870
that the old man's
not too happy with our move.

07:59.914 --> 08:01.872
Fuck him.
This is an internal dispute.

08:01.916 --> 08:04.135
I'll wet his beak.
Gambino will be fine.

08:04.179 --> 08:06.311
Where are we at
with the skim on the movie?

08:06.355 --> 08:07.835
CAESAR:
I met with the union reps.

08:07.878 --> 08:09.706
They're all kicking up to us.The drivers?

08:09.750 --> 08:11.012
CAESAR: [chuckles]
Even better.

08:11.055 --> 08:13.144
Every department in this movie
has its own union.

08:13.188 --> 08:14.494
They're like capos.

08:14.537 --> 08:15.843
We're getting a taste
from all of them.

08:15.886 --> 08:18.193
What about Ruddy,
he doesn't get a taste?

08:18.236 --> 08:20.543
That's what they're saying.

08:20.587 --> 08:22.806
All right, good work.
[clears throat]

08:22.850 --> 08:25.069
Let me know how we're doing
with the collections.

08:25.113 --> 08:27.507
We get Gambino his cut,
keep him calm.

08:27.550 --> 08:30.031
[tense music]

08:30.074 --> 08:31.685
DEAN: I need more money.

08:33.251 --> 08:35.515
For the wall
around the compound.

08:35.558 --> 08:37.734
You said it was doable.
Styrofoam and paint.

08:37.778 --> 08:39.997
Well, the city is making
me build a real wall

08:40.041 --> 08:41.346
to pass inspection.

08:41.390 --> 08:42.870
It's ridiculous.

08:42.913 --> 08:45.394
If I do, I won't have
enough money left over

08:45.437 --> 08:47.527
for the rest of the shoot.

08:49.485 --> 08:51.052
Here's what you do,

08:51.095 --> 08:52.836
build four feet
on either side of the entrance

08:52.880 --> 08:54.882
and make the rest
Styrofoam and paint.

08:54.925 --> 08:56.623
If they find out
and want to fine us,

08:56.666 --> 08:58.799
I'll deal with it then.

08:59.626 --> 09:00.844
[scoffs]

09:03.499 --> 09:05.109
We have a big problem.

09:05.153 --> 09:07.677
Are there are any little ones?Andrea called.

09:07.721 --> 09:09.810
We lost the actor who
was gonna play Luca Brasi.

09:09.853 --> 09:10.767
What?

09:10.811 --> 09:12.508
What are you talking about?

09:12.552 --> 09:13.553
What do you mean,
"We lost him"?

09:13.596 --> 09:15.032
There's a signed contract--

09:15.076 --> 09:16.512
He's dead.

09:16.556 --> 09:18.688
A stroke this morning.Jesus.

09:18.732 --> 09:20.211
Does that mean we need
to cut the scene?

09:20.255 --> 09:21.735
FRANCIS: No, no, no.

09:21.778 --> 09:23.606
Absolutely not.
We're not cutting the scene.

09:23.650 --> 09:25.695
Unless we can
find another 6'6",

09:25.739 --> 09:28.393
300-pound actor
just hanging around...

09:28.437 --> 09:31.135
[gasps, snaps]

09:31.179 --> 09:33.311
What about your friend?

09:33.355 --> 09:35.792
My friend?

09:35.836 --> 09:39.056
BETTYE: "I am honored
and grateful..."

09:39.100 --> 09:43.887
Don Corleone,
I am honored and...

09:43.931 --> 09:45.628
"Grateful."

09:45.672 --> 09:47.238
Right, right.

09:47.282 --> 09:48.675
Don Corleone,

09:48.718 --> 09:51.678
I am honored
and grateful that...

09:51.721 --> 09:54.245
"That you invited me."

09:54.289 --> 09:56.117
Okay, okay.

09:56.160 --> 09:59.816
Don Corleone,
I am honored and...

09:59.860 --> 10:01.949
Oh, my God.
What the fuck, Lenny?

10:01.992 --> 10:04.299
How many times did your
mother drop you on your head?

10:04.342 --> 10:06.867
"I am honored and grateful
that you invited me

10:06.910 --> 10:09.478
into your home on the day
of your daughter's wedding."

10:09.521 --> 10:10.610
Well, why don't you do it?

10:10.653 --> 10:11.915
'Cause they need
a fat fuck like you.

10:11.959 --> 10:13.569
Hey.

10:13.613 --> 10:15.266
It's okay,
we're gonna try again.

10:15.310 --> 10:16.746
Unbelievable.

10:16.790 --> 10:19.619
A head that big and it
can't hold a goddamn thing.

10:19.662 --> 10:21.185
Can we cut down the lines?

10:21.229 --> 10:22.926
Make it easier?

10:22.970 --> 10:26.060
Luca Brasi is formal.

10:26.103 --> 10:28.584
He wants to get the lines
just right for the Don.

10:28.628 --> 10:30.107
He's nervous.

10:30.151 --> 10:32.762
So on the day, we shoot him
right outside the office.

10:32.806 --> 10:34.546
And he's practicing
with his cards.

10:34.590 --> 10:36.374
"Honored and grateful..."

10:36.418 --> 10:38.812
And we shoot it like that.

10:43.512 --> 10:44.556
[cat purring]

10:44.600 --> 10:46.820
Oh, kitty. Oh, kitty-kitty.

10:46.863 --> 10:48.952
What a pretty kitty, huh?

10:48.996 --> 10:51.912
Who's a pretty cat?
[clicking tongue]

10:56.394 --> 10:57.787
What's with the cat?

10:57.831 --> 10:59.876
Did you do a rewrite?

10:59.920 --> 11:02.749
No, there's no cat
in the scene.

11:02.792 --> 11:04.489
That sure looks like a cat.

11:04.533 --> 11:05.708
[clicking tongue]

11:05.752 --> 11:07.057
RUDDY: Is it Brando's cat?

11:07.101 --> 11:08.537
It's one of the stray cats
from the alley

11:08.580 --> 11:09.712
behind the studio.

11:09.756 --> 11:12.846
[mumbling]

11:14.021 --> 11:16.023
I like it.

11:16.066 --> 11:18.852
Yeah, me too.

11:18.895 --> 11:20.723
Of course, 'cause neither one
of you wants to be the one

11:20.767 --> 11:22.856
to tell Brando
he can't have it.

11:23.726 --> 11:25.075
True.
[laughs]

11:25.119 --> 11:26.511
FRED: So what are we doing?

11:26.555 --> 11:28.600
Cat or no cat?

11:28.644 --> 11:30.254
I think it's inspired.

11:30.298 --> 11:31.516
Can we try one?

11:31.560 --> 11:32.822
Okay, let's lock it up.

11:32.866 --> 11:34.868
Last looks, everybody.

11:34.911 --> 11:37.131
Hey, we got a small problem.Yeah?

11:38.393 --> 11:41.352
[cat purring]

11:41.396 --> 11:43.267
Huh.

11:43.311 --> 11:44.616
We'll fix it in post.

11:44.660 --> 11:45.966
Sorry, sir.

11:46.009 --> 11:48.359
Mr. Evans is
on the phone in your office.

11:48.403 --> 11:50.666
He said it can't wait.

11:50.710 --> 11:52.624
[sighs]

11:52.668 --> 11:54.670
Okay, put us on a bell.

11:54.714 --> 11:55.758
[bell rings]

11:55.802 --> 11:58.413
And action.

11:58.456 --> 11:59.588
Bob?

11:59.631 --> 12:01.024
Where are you?

12:01.068 --> 12:02.852
Where am I?
I don't fucking know.

12:02.896 --> 12:04.462
I'm over one
of those square states.

12:04.506 --> 12:05.855
Look, we've got a problem.

12:05.899 --> 12:08.118
Bluhdorn
and Lapidus saw dailies

12:08.162 --> 12:09.772
of Pacino's first day,
and they want to fire him.

12:09.816 --> 12:12.166
What the fuck? No, no.

12:12.209 --> 12:13.820
Look, we're not
changing horses now.

12:13.863 --> 12:15.256
BOB: This is all Lapidus, man.

12:15.299 --> 12:17.127
Barry's a fucking rat
who's always wanted my job,

12:17.171 --> 12:18.433
and this is part
of his power grab.

12:18.476 --> 12:20.783
Okay, listen,
I know you haven't always been

12:20.827 --> 12:22.480
the biggest supporter
of Pacino, but--

12:22.524 --> 12:24.047
Never mind that.

12:24.091 --> 12:26.833
Pacino's our boy now,
so let's not fuck this up.

12:26.876 --> 12:29.749
I told Bluhdorn
we'll talk when I land,

12:29.792 --> 12:31.576
but you need
to figure something out, man.

12:31.620 --> 12:33.665
RUDDY: All right, I'll get
back to set and deal with it.

12:33.709 --> 12:35.145
But first...

12:35.189 --> 12:36.494
how was Texas?

12:40.368 --> 12:42.065
Bob?

12:42.109 --> 12:45.373
Hot as a fucking sauna.

12:45.416 --> 12:46.940
See ya.

12:51.945 --> 12:55.165
[somber music]

12:55.209 --> 12:57.080
MARLON: Power in and of itself

12:57.124 --> 12:58.908
is not an important thing
to him.

12:58.952 --> 13:01.737
You know, he would never
talk about his own power.

13:01.781 --> 13:03.783
FRANCIS: No, his power
comes from his confidence,

13:03.826 --> 13:05.785
from what he
doesn't have to say.

13:05.828 --> 13:07.961
MARLON:
And he's not a criminal.

13:08.004 --> 13:10.615
He's got a deep moral center.

13:10.659 --> 13:12.704
Politicians are the criminals,

13:12.748 --> 13:14.402
the drug dealers
getting people hooked

13:14.445 --> 13:15.359
on empty promises.

13:15.403 --> 13:16.621
Mm-hmm.

13:16.665 --> 13:18.710
The Don,
he serves his community

13:18.754 --> 13:20.800
more than any
politician ever would.

13:20.843 --> 13:22.714
Yes, he does.

13:22.758 --> 13:24.107
And when people
come for his help,

13:24.151 --> 13:25.282
he knows right from wrong

13:25.326 --> 13:27.371
because of his
old world values.

13:27.415 --> 13:30.548
He just wants to do right
by his people and his family.

13:31.723 --> 13:34.030
Yeah, that's it.
That's exactly it.

13:34.074 --> 13:35.466
You want to try another one?

13:35.510 --> 13:36.990
All right.
Okay.

13:37.033 --> 13:38.948
Freddie.FRED: Okay, lock it up.

13:38.992 --> 13:41.385
Going again.
Last looks, please.

13:43.910 --> 13:45.737
What the fuck
is Duvall wearing?

13:45.781 --> 13:47.652
Oh, Brando likes
to be in the moment.

13:47.696 --> 13:49.524
He doesn't memorize his lines.

13:49.567 --> 13:51.656
Apparently no one does.

13:51.700 --> 13:54.050
Listen,
I just talked to Bob.

13:54.094 --> 13:56.444
Charlie and Lapidus
want to fire Pacino.

13:56.487 --> 13:58.489
[loudly] What?

13:58.533 --> 14:01.579
Um, one second, Freddie.

14:01.623 --> 14:03.190
What are you talking about?

14:03.233 --> 14:05.061
They saw the dailies
from his first scene.

14:05.105 --> 14:06.497
They're not happy.

14:06.541 --> 14:08.848
They don't even
know how to look at dailies.

14:08.891 --> 14:10.501
What do--how can
they judge him on one scene?

14:10.545 --> 14:12.677
Look, we just need
to get them excited about him.

14:12.721 --> 14:14.723
What's his best scene?

14:14.766 --> 14:16.507
There's a lot.

14:16.551 --> 14:17.900
Um...

14:17.944 --> 14:19.206
what about the restaurant scene

14:19.249 --> 14:20.990
where he shoots
Sollozzo and McCluskey?

14:21.034 --> 14:22.862
I mean, they gotta be able
to see what he can do there.

14:22.905 --> 14:24.428
Perfect.
When do we shoot that?

14:24.472 --> 14:26.474
[sighs]
End of the week.

14:27.736 --> 14:29.694
We need to shoot that tomorrow.

14:30.521 --> 14:32.175
Fine, yes, fine.
I can do that, yes.

14:32.219 --> 14:33.829
See if we can get the location.

14:33.873 --> 14:35.657
Yes.Gordy.

14:35.700 --> 14:37.615
Let me chat with you.

14:37.659 --> 14:39.530
You too, Aram.

14:39.574 --> 14:41.054
ARAM: What do you need, boss?

14:41.097 --> 14:43.578
[quietly]
Okay, new policy.

14:43.621 --> 14:47.060
As of right now, only the four
of us have access to dailies.

14:47.103 --> 14:50.106
No one else sees them
unless Francis or I approve it.

14:51.760 --> 14:53.631
You got it.Yeah, yeah.

14:56.156 --> 14:58.898
FRANCIS: [sighs]
Freddie.

14:58.941 --> 15:00.812
FRED: Okay, roll sound.

15:00.856 --> 15:03.032
FRANCIS: And action.

15:03.076 --> 15:04.947
Business is good.

15:04.991 --> 15:06.644
This is for you.
20 large.

15:06.688 --> 15:08.603
From the fundraiser.

15:09.734 --> 15:11.171
20, huh?

15:12.302 --> 15:15.262
How many tickets
you sell to that event?

15:18.178 --> 15:20.963
Well, we're
still counting.

15:21.007 --> 15:22.747
This is just
to show respect.

15:22.791 --> 15:24.445
There's more
where that came from.

15:30.973 --> 15:33.889
CARLO: I appreciate that, Joe.

15:33.933 --> 15:37.414
I had my concerns about this...

15:37.458 --> 15:40.722
Italian League thing of yours
from the very beginning.

15:40.765 --> 15:42.767
But I gotta say,

15:42.811 --> 15:44.639
you're proving me wrong.

15:46.641 --> 15:48.251
Yeah, well,

15:48.295 --> 15:50.427
the unions at the movie
have started to produce too.

15:50.471 --> 15:51.951
I'll have
your cut on Friday.

15:51.994 --> 15:53.430
It was good that we
got in on this thing

15:53.474 --> 15:54.605
from the ground up.

15:56.694 --> 15:58.522
You're doing great, Joe.

15:58.566 --> 16:00.481
Mm? Keep it up.

16:03.005 --> 16:05.138
Okay.

16:07.879 --> 16:10.795
[ominous music]

16:10.839 --> 16:17.977
♪

16:28.857 --> 16:30.641
GALLO: This kind of trouble,

16:30.685 --> 16:31.903
it's just the beginning.

16:31.947 --> 16:33.122
Kiss my ass.Come on.

16:33.166 --> 16:34.297
The lighting's not working.

16:34.341 --> 16:36.082
We're falling way behind.

16:36.125 --> 16:37.648
GORDY: The lighting's perfect.

16:37.692 --> 16:39.041
It's perfect!

16:39.085 --> 16:40.173
But if you don't
direct the actors,

16:40.216 --> 16:42.349
none of it
means a fucking thing!

16:42.392 --> 16:43.915
RUDDY: [quietly]
Clear the set.

16:43.959 --> 16:45.091
FRANCIS:
So precious about everything.

16:45.134 --> 16:47.528
I give a shit
what it looks like!

16:47.571 --> 16:48.790
Oh--
Okay, everybody.

16:48.833 --> 16:50.270
Take five.
[bell rings]

16:50.313 --> 16:51.967
More fucking drama
than a soap opera.

16:52.011 --> 16:53.447
They're not
on the same page.

16:53.490 --> 16:55.014
Mm-hmm, not even reading
the same book.

16:55.057 --> 16:56.450
Coppola's lost this crew.

16:56.493 --> 16:58.843
We have to tell
Charlie about this.

16:58.887 --> 17:00.454
GORDY: Is that
what you think, man?

17:00.497 --> 17:03.283
FRANCIS: Of course I care
about what it looks like!

17:03.326 --> 17:05.328
But the actors, they can't even
walk around the set!

17:05.372 --> 17:08.027
Yes, that's right.
They can't.

17:08.070 --> 17:09.985
They have to hit their marks!

17:10.029 --> 17:11.595
That's the point!

17:11.639 --> 17:13.510
Unless you just want me
to point a 10K at the room

17:13.554 --> 17:14.946
and walk away.

17:14.990 --> 17:17.166
You know lighting!

17:17.210 --> 17:19.821
You don't know a goddamn thing
about the needs of actors.

17:19.864 --> 17:21.431
They need freedom.

17:21.475 --> 17:23.694
They need to be able
to walk around

17:23.738 --> 17:25.609
so they can bring
the characters to life.

17:25.653 --> 17:27.350
We talked about this.
How simply can I put this?

17:27.394 --> 17:30.353
So there's light,
and there's dark.

17:30.397 --> 17:32.703
If they're not in the light,
they're in the dark!

17:32.747 --> 17:34.923
RUDDY: All right, hey, boys,
bring it down a notch.

17:34.966 --> 17:36.446
Okay, let me
make it simple for you.

17:36.490 --> 17:39.058
Anybody coming to see
this movie is not gonna care

17:39.101 --> 17:40.798
about your lights
if they can't connect

17:40.842 --> 17:42.148
with the actors!

17:42.191 --> 17:44.367
You're impossible.
You are impossible.

17:44.411 --> 17:46.630
Nobody can talk to you!

17:46.674 --> 17:48.023
FRANCIS: I'll light it.

17:48.067 --> 17:49.459
I can light it!

17:49.503 --> 17:50.547
[chair clatters]

17:50.591 --> 17:51.766
Look at this guy!

17:51.809 --> 17:53.594
Let him go.
No, let him go!

17:55.117 --> 17:57.119
Gordy, come on--No, no!

17:57.163 --> 17:58.903
He's being an asshole.

17:58.947 --> 18:00.557
He acts like this is just
between him and the actors.

18:00.601 --> 18:02.516
There's 150 fucking people
on this crew

18:02.559 --> 18:04.431
busting their asses,
trying to make this work

18:04.474 --> 18:05.823
for him!

18:05.867 --> 18:07.260
He has no appreciation
for anyone,

18:07.303 --> 18:08.565
and I'm done with it, I'm done.

18:08.609 --> 18:10.089
Okay, well, listen to me,
Gordy, you leave,

18:10.132 --> 18:12.091
there's a good chance those
150 people are unemployed.

18:12.134 --> 18:14.223
Okay, so I'll fix this, okay?[scoffs]

18:14.267 --> 18:16.095
But you gotta give me
a chance to do it, okay?

18:16.138 --> 18:17.661
Please.

18:20.186 --> 18:21.535
I'll finish the day,

18:21.578 --> 18:24.755
but that's it
unless he apologizes.

18:24.799 --> 18:26.366
Fuck.
[sighs]

18:26.409 --> 18:27.845
Damn it.

18:32.937 --> 18:34.113
Coppola thinks he's a god,

18:34.156 --> 18:35.462
but the product is a mess.

18:35.505 --> 18:38.073
First Pacino, now everything's
incredibly dark,

18:38.117 --> 18:39.683
and Brando
is a mumbling fool.

18:39.727 --> 18:41.903
ARAM: The scene Coppola shot
in the Don's office

18:41.946 --> 18:43.992
is unusable.

18:44.035 --> 18:45.950
Star of the scene
is a goddamn cat.

18:45.994 --> 18:47.822
The DP is this
close to quitting,

18:47.865 --> 18:49.606
and the crew is not far behind.

18:50.999 --> 18:53.132
So what's our solution?

18:53.175 --> 18:54.959
We need to get rid of Coppola.

18:55.003 --> 18:57.048
Right after we
get rid of Pacino.

18:57.092 --> 18:58.137
Aram should take the helm.

18:58.180 --> 18:59.442
He's been on set
the whole time.

18:59.486 --> 19:01.923
He knows the footage.
He can fix this.

19:07.146 --> 19:08.625
Fine.

19:08.669 --> 19:12.890
Put together the worst set
of dailies you possibly can.

19:12.934 --> 19:15.763
We'll show Charlie,
and if it's what you say...

19:15.806 --> 19:17.286
[soft music]

19:17.330 --> 19:19.593
The two of you
better be ready to take over.

19:19.636 --> 19:21.508
♪

19:21.551 --> 19:24.119
Good.

19:24.163 --> 19:26.165
I don't apologize to anybody.

19:26.208 --> 19:27.688
Unless it's my mother.

19:27.731 --> 19:29.820
And even if I had a reason
to apologize to her,

19:29.864 --> 19:32.388
my father would kill me
before I had the chance.

19:32.432 --> 19:35.261
A lot
of people want us to fail.

19:35.304 --> 19:38.133
And even more
of them want you to fail.

19:38.177 --> 19:40.004
I'm aware, thank you.

19:40.048 --> 19:42.311
Gordy isn't one
of those people.

19:42.355 --> 19:45.749
[sighs]
He's not hearing me.

19:46.881 --> 19:48.143
Francis, listen to me.

19:48.187 --> 19:49.753
You're the director
of this film.

19:49.797 --> 19:50.928
Mm-hmm.

19:50.972 --> 19:52.321
But you can't
achieve your vision

19:52.365 --> 19:54.671
unless you have the crew
on your side.

19:56.107 --> 19:58.545
You can't do it
all on your own.

19:58.588 --> 20:01.939
You need them,
and you really need Gordy.

20:03.245 --> 20:05.552
So do the right thing
and apologize.

20:07.249 --> 20:09.686
Just pretend he's your mother.

20:12.602 --> 20:14.169
I...

20:14.213 --> 20:16.389
Thank you.

20:16.432 --> 20:18.826
[sighs]BOB: Hey, Ruddy!

20:18.869 --> 20:20.741
There he is, there he is.

20:20.784 --> 20:22.438
My favorite producer.

20:22.482 --> 20:23.874
RUDDY: I didn't know
you were coming today.

20:23.918 --> 20:25.572
Yeah, why not?We're on the last scene now.

20:25.615 --> 20:26.747
And then we're wrapped
for the day.

20:26.790 --> 20:28.227
Good, 'cause we're
going out, bubbie.

20:28.270 --> 20:29.619
Grab your coat,

20:29.663 --> 20:31.317
and maybe spritz yourself
with some cologne.

20:31.360 --> 20:32.796
You got that sweat smell.
[exhales sharply]

20:32.840 --> 20:34.276
It's called working.

20:34.320 --> 20:36.278
Where are we going?We're going out.

20:36.322 --> 20:38.280
We're gonna fuck
this town in half!

20:38.324 --> 20:39.803
[exhales sharply]

20:39.847 --> 20:42.893
♪ [Mountain's
"Mississippi Queen"]

20:42.937 --> 20:49.944
♪

20:53.121 --> 20:54.949
Whoa.

20:54.992 --> 20:57.473
♪ Mississippi Queen

20:57.517 --> 20:59.736
♪ If you know what I mean

20:59.780 --> 21:01.347
[indistinct chatter]

21:01.390 --> 21:04.263
♪ Mississippi Queen

21:04.306 --> 21:05.307
♪ She taught me everything

21:05.351 --> 21:07.483
This way.

21:07.527 --> 21:10.965
♪ Went down
around Vicksburg ♪

21:11.008 --> 21:14.403
♪ Around Louisiana way

21:14.447 --> 21:16.927
♪ Where lived
the Cajun Lady ♪

21:16.971 --> 21:18.799
♪

21:18.842 --> 21:21.367
Bring it.

21:21.410 --> 21:24.544
♪ You know
she was a dancer ♪

21:24.587 --> 21:26.589
♪ She moved better on wine

21:26.633 --> 21:29.113
♪ While the rest
of them dudes ♪

21:29.157 --> 21:31.290
Ruddy.
Welcome to paradise.

21:31.333 --> 21:32.900
Shall we?

21:32.943 --> 21:35.119
I think so.

21:35.163 --> 21:36.773
Sure you know
what you're doing?

21:36.817 --> 21:39.994
If I don't,
maybe they'll teach me.

21:40.037 --> 21:41.648
Lighten up, Ruddy.

21:41.691 --> 21:43.519
We're shooting a movie.
We're the kings of New York.

21:43.563 --> 21:45.521
You know what kings do?

21:45.565 --> 21:48.176
Whatever the fuck we want.

21:48.219 --> 21:50.613
Let's have some fun,
right, girls?

21:50.657 --> 21:53.616
♪

21:53.660 --> 21:57.359
Come all ye faithful!
That's it, mama, bring it in.

21:57.403 --> 22:00.144
Show me the hoops you
got on the dance floor.

22:00.188 --> 22:01.450
Come on, Ruddy!

22:01.494 --> 22:02.973
That's it,
show me the hoops.

22:03.017 --> 22:04.627
Oh, yeah.

22:04.671 --> 22:07.761
♪ [Rare Earth's
"Nice Place To Visit"]

22:07.804 --> 22:14.768
♪

22:29.609 --> 22:32.351
♪ Well, it's a real nice
place to visit ♪

22:32.394 --> 22:34.788
♪ But you wouldn't want
to live here ♪

22:34.831 --> 22:37.834
♪

22:37.878 --> 22:39.314
Did you lose someone?

22:39.358 --> 22:40.968
Yeah, the guy came with.

22:41.011 --> 22:42.665
He's tall, dark...

22:42.709 --> 22:44.319
emotionally unstable.

22:44.363 --> 22:46.843
Ah, "The King."

22:46.887 --> 22:48.323
RUDDY: Yeah, sure.

22:48.367 --> 22:49.846
♪

22:49.890 --> 22:52.414
He left with his twin subjects
ten minutes ago.

22:52.458 --> 22:54.895
Ah, fuck.

22:54.938 --> 22:57.245
If you're worried about
him making it home, don't.

22:57.288 --> 22:59.203
He's not going home.
[chuckles]

22:59.247 --> 23:01.118
Yeah...

23:01.162 --> 23:02.685
have we met?

23:02.729 --> 23:06.123
No, but I saw you
on the dance floor.

23:06.167 --> 23:08.430
Oh, great.

23:08.474 --> 23:09.779
♪

23:09.823 --> 23:13.043
I'm not a very good dancer.

23:13.087 --> 23:15.176
No argument there.
[laughs]

23:15.219 --> 23:16.438
[laughs]

23:16.482 --> 23:18.222
♪

23:18.266 --> 23:21.225
I'm Al.

23:21.269 --> 23:23.358
Rosie.

23:23.402 --> 23:25.404
♪

23:25.447 --> 23:27.057
You come here often?

23:27.101 --> 23:30.234
[laughs] Really?

23:30.278 --> 23:32.454
Genuine question.

23:32.498 --> 23:34.500
Only for work.

23:34.543 --> 23:36.676
What do you do?

23:37.590 --> 23:39.548
I designed it.

23:39.592 --> 23:41.724
Which part?

23:41.768 --> 23:43.900
♪

23:43.944 --> 23:46.468
All of it.

23:46.512 --> 23:48.775
Very impressive.

23:48.818 --> 23:52.126
♪

23:52.169 --> 23:54.128
You want to get out of here?

23:54.171 --> 23:56.347
♪ Nice place to visit

23:56.391 --> 23:58.741
RUDDY: Take the Mona Lisa,
for example.

23:58.785 --> 24:01.788
Arguably the most famous
painting of all time, right?

24:01.831 --> 24:03.485
But that was only
after it got stolen

24:03.529 --> 24:05.095
before the First World War.

24:05.139 --> 24:06.662
It got a lot of press.

24:06.706 --> 24:08.490
And it's a good painting.

24:08.534 --> 24:10.927
It's great, you know?
The enigmatic smile.

24:10.971 --> 24:15.105
All that, but is it the best?
I don't know.

24:15.149 --> 24:18.369
For me, personally,
it doesn't exactly...

24:18.413 --> 24:20.589
Inspire you.
Yeah.

24:20.633 --> 24:22.896
But that's because
I don't know any better.

24:22.939 --> 24:24.550
Oh, you don't have
to know anything about art

24:24.593 --> 24:25.986
to appreciate it.

24:26.813 --> 24:29.293
You ever see the moon landing?

24:29.337 --> 24:31.252
Who didn't?Inspiring, huh?

24:33.210 --> 24:35.299
How do the rockets work?

24:35.343 --> 24:36.475
How did they land?

24:36.518 --> 24:37.650
How do they

24:37.693 --> 24:39.434
know how to make
their way back

24:39.478 --> 24:41.480
to this tiny planet?

24:44.352 --> 24:46.528
I don't know, either.
[laughs]

24:46.572 --> 24:49.009
But we don't have to know.

24:49.052 --> 24:51.054
We can just...

24:51.098 --> 24:54.188
enjoy the spectacular
wonder of it all.

25:05.416 --> 25:06.940
Hey.

25:06.983 --> 25:08.332
Hey!

25:08.376 --> 25:09.508
What are you still doing here?

25:09.551 --> 25:10.813
My grandmother
told me to never

25:10.857 --> 25:12.293
let a woman walk
home alone at night,

25:12.336 --> 25:14.513
so here I am.

25:14.556 --> 25:17.472
So you've just
been waiting for me?

25:17.516 --> 25:19.343
Yeah.

25:19.387 --> 25:20.736
[chuckles]
How chivalrous.

25:20.780 --> 25:22.521
Yeah, I know.
[laughs]

25:22.564 --> 25:23.609
Where do you live?

25:23.652 --> 25:24.566
I don't want to take you
out of your way.

25:24.610 --> 25:25.654
No, no, no, that's okay.

25:25.698 --> 25:26.960
I live in Brooklyn,

25:27.003 --> 25:29.440
same house
I grew up in, actually.

25:29.484 --> 25:31.573
Really?Yeah, my grandma's real old.

25:31.617 --> 25:34.837
So I stop in from time to time,
make sure she's okay, you know?

25:34.881 --> 25:36.970
That's very sweet.Yeah.

25:37.013 --> 25:38.885
My mom died when me
and my brother were real young,

25:38.928 --> 25:40.539
so she's the one
that raised us.

25:41.670 --> 25:43.019
It's home.[scoffs]

25:43.063 --> 25:44.064
Yeah, it'd be nice if there was

25:44.107 --> 25:45.413
one nice bed
in the house, but--

25:45.456 --> 25:46.675
Hey!
Hey!

25:46.719 --> 25:48.068
Where do you think
you're going?

25:48.111 --> 25:49.678
[grunts]

25:49.722 --> 25:51.375
Oh, my God!

25:51.419 --> 25:54.335
[grunts, blows landing]

25:58.165 --> 25:59.601
[gasps]

25:59.645 --> 26:01.603
[shakily]
Holy shit.

26:01.647 --> 26:04.563
[tense music]

26:04.606 --> 26:09.611
♪

26:09.655 --> 26:11.352
You all right?

26:15.443 --> 26:16.705
What happened?

26:16.749 --> 26:18.881
It's just my watch.

26:18.925 --> 26:21.144
It's fine.

26:21.188 --> 26:22.885
I'm okay, thank you.

26:22.929 --> 26:24.974
[train squeals in distance]

26:25.018 --> 26:26.933
If I'm going
to consider dating you,

26:26.976 --> 26:29.675
I have to know
some things about you.

26:33.417 --> 26:35.811
Ask me anything you want.

26:35.855 --> 26:38.335
Are you an honest man?

26:38.379 --> 26:41.077
Yeah, I am.

26:41.121 --> 26:42.731
Are you married?

26:42.775 --> 26:45.299
No.
But you were.

26:45.342 --> 26:47.214
It's complicated.

26:47.257 --> 26:48.694
No doubt.

26:48.737 --> 26:51.610
[soft music playing]

26:51.653 --> 26:55.265
So what do you do, Al, hm?

26:55.309 --> 26:57.093
Movies.

26:57.137 --> 26:58.573
I make movies.

26:58.617 --> 27:00.401
So you're a director.

27:00.444 --> 27:03.273
No, I'm the producer.

27:03.317 --> 27:05.232
So you write the script?

27:05.275 --> 27:06.712
No.

27:06.755 --> 27:10.106
But I put it all together.

27:10.150 --> 27:12.282
[chuckling]
What does that mean?

27:12.326 --> 27:14.284
♪

27:14.328 --> 27:15.895
Tell you what.

27:15.938 --> 27:17.723
Why don't you come
to set tomorrow,

27:17.766 --> 27:20.029
and I'll show you what I do?

27:20.073 --> 27:22.945
♪

27:22.989 --> 27:26.688
Well, I guess you just got
yourself a second date.

27:26.732 --> 27:32.651
♪

27:32.694 --> 27:34.783
[lively music]

27:34.827 --> 27:36.306
There's my guys.

27:36.350 --> 27:38.831
Hey, saw everything from
yesterday, looks really good.

27:38.874 --> 27:40.659
I hope so.How's the coffee?

27:40.702 --> 27:42.965
Mm, shit.Terrific.

27:43.009 --> 27:45.881
[chuckles]
It's always shit.

27:45.925 --> 27:47.666
Hey, buddy, do me a favor.

27:47.709 --> 27:49.580
I got a girl coming
to set today,

27:49.624 --> 27:50.799
I need you to keep
an eye out for her.

27:50.843 --> 27:51.931
All right, you got it, Al.

27:51.974 --> 27:54.063
Oh, and don't hit on her.

27:54.107 --> 27:55.108
No promises.

27:55.151 --> 27:58.154
FRANCIS:
Has anyone seen Pacino?

27:58.198 --> 27:59.460
He's right there.

28:01.810 --> 28:03.594
Why is he not in wardrobe?

28:03.638 --> 28:04.900
I don't know,
but the kid better bring

28:04.944 --> 28:06.641
his A game today,
otherwise we're fucked.

28:06.685 --> 28:08.338
[clears throat]
Hey, Al.

28:08.382 --> 28:10.906
How are you?
Hey, Al.

28:10.950 --> 28:13.343
Francis, can we talk
for a second, please?

28:13.387 --> 28:14.867
Yeah, of course.

28:16.956 --> 28:19.828
Francis, why'd we
move the scene up today?

28:21.787 --> 28:24.311
I just wanted
to give you a chance to shine.

28:24.354 --> 28:26.313
Uh-huh, yeah.

28:26.356 --> 28:28.707
They, uh....

28:28.750 --> 28:31.318
they want to fire me,
don't they?

28:34.451 --> 28:36.845
Listen to me.
Look at me.

28:36.889 --> 28:38.760
We're not gonna
let that happen to you.

28:38.804 --> 28:40.370
Uh-huh.

28:40.414 --> 28:41.894
Mm-hmm?
Mm-hmm.

28:41.937 --> 28:43.504
Okay.Come here,

28:43.547 --> 28:45.941
I want to show you something.

28:47.813 --> 28:49.858
All right.

28:49.902 --> 28:52.382
Props? Who's back there?

28:52.426 --> 28:54.776
Bruno? Hey, pal.

28:54.820 --> 28:56.125
Do me a favor.

28:56.169 --> 28:59.650
Give us a moment.
Thank you, sir.

28:59.694 --> 29:03.045
Okay, so...

29:03.089 --> 29:05.787
when you come in here,

29:05.831 --> 29:09.530
I want you
to be extremely nervous.

29:09.573 --> 29:11.532
That shouldn't be a stretch,
Francis.

29:11.575 --> 29:13.142
Mm-hmm, gotcha.

29:13.186 --> 29:16.319
Out there, you're trying
very hard not to show it.

29:16.363 --> 29:18.452
But in here,
the reality of it all,

29:18.495 --> 29:21.281
it hits you here, okay?

29:21.324 --> 29:23.805
Take a moment.
Mm-hmm.

29:23.849 --> 29:25.764
This is where
you gotta step up.

29:25.807 --> 29:28.505
[soft music]

29:28.549 --> 29:31.639
This bathroom,

29:31.682 --> 29:33.946
this is the birthplace
of the future

29:33.989 --> 29:36.600
Don Michael Corleone.

29:36.644 --> 29:40.517
♪

29:40.561 --> 29:42.998
Come in here.

29:43.042 --> 29:44.521
Where's the gun gonna be, here?

29:44.565 --> 29:45.871
Behind the tank.

29:47.089 --> 29:49.831
Go ahead, try it out.All right.

29:49.875 --> 29:53.661
But I do want a moment
before you go for the gun.

29:53.704 --> 29:55.054
Uh-huh.
Okay?

29:55.097 --> 29:58.057
So you look up,
you see the tank.

29:58.100 --> 30:01.277
You don't know, was Clemenza
even able to plant it?

30:01.321 --> 30:02.713
Right?
Mm-hmm.

30:02.757 --> 30:03.802
That's the motivation.

30:03.845 --> 30:06.630
Then, you go for the gun.

30:06.674 --> 30:08.284
Where should I put it?

30:08.328 --> 30:09.938
My pocket, my belt,
what do you think?

30:09.982 --> 30:11.418
Where does it feel
natural for you?

30:11.461 --> 30:13.289
Put it wherever feels right.

30:14.769 --> 30:16.858
So I'm gonna take it,
I'm gonna--

30:16.902 --> 30:18.207
In here, we're nervous.

30:18.251 --> 30:20.079
Out there, we're playing
somebody trying...

30:20.122 --> 30:20.993
not to be nervous.Not to be nervous.

30:21.036 --> 30:22.081
Not--there you go.

30:22.124 --> 30:23.604
All right.
Go get dressed.

30:23.647 --> 30:25.040
Okay, okay.
You got it.

30:25.084 --> 30:28.217
Yep, okay, thank you,
Francis, all right.

30:30.437 --> 30:33.179
[sighs]

30:33.222 --> 30:35.964
Bruno.

30:36.008 --> 30:37.661
Do me a favor.

30:37.705 --> 30:39.663
When you put
the gun back there,

30:39.707 --> 30:41.056
don't put it there.

30:41.100 --> 30:42.928
Put it to the left.

30:42.971 --> 30:45.495
Yeah, and like 6 inches higher.

30:45.539 --> 30:46.757
That's perfect.

30:46.801 --> 30:48.498
Do not tell him.

30:48.542 --> 30:50.892
Okay? Good man.

30:50.936 --> 30:52.676
RUDDY: You picked a good day.

30:52.720 --> 30:54.896
I mean, this is one of my
favorite scenes in the film.

30:54.940 --> 30:57.116
So Michael's
about to sit down to dinner

30:57.159 --> 30:59.335
with these two guys
who tried to kill his father.

30:59.379 --> 31:02.338
They want peace.
Michael wants revenge.

31:02.382 --> 31:05.341
Oh, so this is a gangster film.

31:05.385 --> 31:06.995
It's more than that.

31:07.039 --> 31:08.954
I'm sorry,
I still don't really know

31:08.997 --> 31:10.564
what it is that you do.

31:10.607 --> 31:12.044
CHARLIE: Ruddy!

31:12.087 --> 31:14.350
Hey, Charlie, I didn't know
you were coming today.

31:14.394 --> 31:17.527
Yeah, I saw the dailies.
They're terrible.

31:17.571 --> 31:19.703
They're too dark, and what's
with the fucking cat?

31:19.747 --> 31:22.271
I couldn't hear a goddamn
thing over all that purring.

31:22.315 --> 31:24.012
They weren't ready
for you to see, Charlie.

31:24.056 --> 31:26.014
They still need to be
color timed and engineered,

31:26.058 --> 31:28.321
but Francis is
getting some amazing footage.

31:28.364 --> 31:30.105
You gotta trust me,
it's gonna be great.

31:30.149 --> 31:31.977
Yeah, well, trust
has to earned, Ruddy.

31:32.020 --> 31:34.370
Let's see what
the little shrimp can do.

31:35.763 --> 31:37.939
Charlie.

31:37.983 --> 31:39.158
They let you out
of the tower, huh?

31:39.201 --> 31:41.551
[chuckles]
You need a bath.

31:41.595 --> 31:46.339
Oh, nonsense, women find
my natural musk intoxicating.

31:46.382 --> 31:48.602
Hey, Bob,
we've still got a little bit

31:48.645 --> 31:50.082
of time before the scene,

31:50.125 --> 31:52.388
so I got a nice trailer set up
for you if you want it.

31:52.432 --> 31:54.390
Oh, I knew you were
a good producer, all right.

31:54.434 --> 31:57.437
Yeah, sure, why not?
Yeah, yeah.

31:57.480 --> 31:59.004
Good.

31:59.047 --> 32:00.788
Take him to mytrailer.

32:00.831 --> 32:03.443
Get him a coffee and water.Copy.

32:03.486 --> 32:05.271
Can I get you anything?

32:05.314 --> 32:08.143
How about a big steaming
pile of elephant shit?

32:08.187 --> 32:10.929
Because this looks
like a goddamn circus.

32:10.972 --> 32:12.539
You know, the thing
about the circus is,

32:12.582 --> 32:14.062
when you're staring at a guy
who put his head

32:14.106 --> 32:15.411
into the mouth of a lion,

32:15.455 --> 32:18.110
you completely forget
about the elephant shit.

32:18.153 --> 32:21.026
Come here.
We've got a problem.

32:21.069 --> 32:24.072
The restaurant owner
wants us out of here.

32:24.116 --> 32:27.597
All right, I'll handle it.
Go handle this.

32:27.641 --> 32:28.990
I'll be right back.

32:29.034 --> 32:30.339
Hey, Charlie.Bettye.

32:30.383 --> 32:33.473
[soft music]

32:33.516 --> 32:36.171
That's the worst smile
you've ever given me.

32:36.215 --> 32:38.434
Only because I didn't mean it.

32:38.478 --> 32:43.483
♪

32:43.526 --> 32:46.747
Hey, get me a martini.

32:46.790 --> 32:49.141
It's not a real bar, sir.

32:49.184 --> 32:51.708
Boys, boys, boys.

32:51.752 --> 32:53.014
[chuckles]

32:53.058 --> 32:55.016
So what do you do on the movie?

32:55.060 --> 32:57.018
I manage.

32:57.062 --> 32:58.715
What do you manage?

32:58.759 --> 33:01.588
Whatever I have to.

33:01.631 --> 33:04.460
It sounds like you and Al
sort of do the same thing.

33:04.504 --> 33:06.114
Yeah.

33:06.158 --> 33:07.986
He just gets paid a lot more.

33:08.029 --> 33:09.639
[chuckles]Ha.

33:09.683 --> 33:10.989
SPIRACHIO: Four hours.

33:11.032 --> 33:13.295
Why, you say four hours,
and it's already been six.

33:13.339 --> 33:15.123
And I gotta get ready
for the dinner crowd now.

33:15.167 --> 33:16.168
Mr. Spirachio,
we're more than happy

33:16.211 --> 33:17.473
to pay you for the extra time.

33:17.517 --> 33:18.997
No, no, no.
I don't want no more money.

33:19.040 --> 33:20.911
I want you out now.

33:20.955 --> 33:22.043
I feel like we
can work something out.

33:22.087 --> 33:23.305
I'm gonna grab
my locations manager.

33:23.349 --> 33:24.741
No, no, no more talking.

33:24.785 --> 33:26.526
I want you to take
all your people

33:26.569 --> 33:28.180
and leave my restaurant!

33:28.223 --> 33:29.833
[speaking Italian]

33:29.877 --> 33:31.531
What is it with this guy?

33:33.098 --> 33:35.013
Okay.

33:35.056 --> 33:37.015
This is Mr. Spirachio.
He owns the restaurant.

33:37.058 --> 33:38.146
How you doing?
Oh, nice place.

33:38.190 --> 33:39.495
No, I want youse out.

33:39.539 --> 33:41.106
We just need
a couple more hours.

33:41.149 --> 33:42.324
Don't let him call anybody.SPIRACHIO: No more hours.

33:42.368 --> 33:44.065
No more minutes.
You had enough.

33:44.109 --> 33:45.980
I want you out.
No, I don't--

33:46.024 --> 33:47.634
Come on, come on.
Hey!

33:47.677 --> 33:50.028
Come on!
Come on--

33:50.071 --> 33:52.073
God damn it,
let me out!

33:52.117 --> 33:54.249
[speaking Italian]

33:59.646 --> 34:01.561
[sighs] Movies.

34:03.780 --> 34:06.566
[tense music]

34:06.609 --> 34:08.176
[door creaks]

34:08.220 --> 34:10.787
[footsteps thudding]

34:10.831 --> 34:12.398
[chair scrapes]

34:12.441 --> 34:16.184
♪

34:16.228 --> 34:18.882
[gunshots]
[body thuds]

34:18.926 --> 34:20.188
[glass shatters]

34:20.232 --> 34:22.712
Don't worry, Charlie.
It's not real.

34:22.756 --> 34:25.585
And cut!

34:26.368 --> 34:28.370
I've never seen you look
at anyone like that before.

34:28.414 --> 34:29.937
I might be a little jealous.

34:29.980 --> 34:32.418
I'm happy he's not
just burning my money.

34:32.461 --> 34:34.246
Come on, Charlie,
admit it, you love him.

34:34.289 --> 34:36.552
I don't love anybody,
but I like him.

34:36.596 --> 34:38.119
I like him.

34:38.163 --> 34:39.555
FRANCIS: Huh?

34:40.469 --> 34:42.863
Al, that was
really something.

34:42.906 --> 34:44.517
♪

34:44.560 --> 34:46.519
Uh...

34:46.562 --> 34:48.303
♪

34:48.347 --> 34:50.566
FRED: All right,
ready to go again.

34:50.610 --> 34:52.916
♪

34:52.960 --> 34:55.571
[laughs] Get over here.

34:55.615 --> 34:57.921
That's what they call
method acting, Charlie.

34:57.965 --> 34:59.184
Thank you, Mr. Hollywood.

34:59.227 --> 35:00.837
So glad you spent time
as a shitty actor

35:00.881 --> 35:03.188
so you can illuminate us all
on useless crap.

35:03.231 --> 35:04.928
[chuckles]
Yeah.

35:04.972 --> 35:06.234
Hey, I think
I'm gonna head out.

35:06.278 --> 35:07.844
You sure?
Yeah.

35:07.888 --> 35:09.150
You don't want
to see more of that?

35:09.194 --> 35:11.457
I've seen more than enough.

35:11.500 --> 35:13.546
All right, I'll walk you out.Thank you.

35:13.589 --> 35:15.591
Thanks so much.

35:17.245 --> 35:19.943
I think I understand
what you do.

35:19.987 --> 35:21.641
You're a problem solver.

35:21.684 --> 35:25.471
You're a ringmaster.Something like that.

35:25.514 --> 35:26.950
Holy shit.

35:26.994 --> 35:28.778
What is this?

35:28.822 --> 35:30.389
That's a prop.

35:32.391 --> 35:35.089
Horses are supposed
to represent courage

35:35.133 --> 35:36.351
and freedom.

35:36.395 --> 35:39.137
And to cut off its head...

35:39.180 --> 35:41.617
that's America right there.

35:41.661 --> 35:43.402
This is art.

35:43.445 --> 35:45.491
I mean,
most women like jewelry,

35:45.534 --> 35:47.623
but if you like it,
you could take it.

35:47.667 --> 35:50.452
Really?Yeah, knock yourself out.

35:50.496 --> 35:52.062
[chuckles]

35:52.106 --> 35:53.803
Great.

35:53.847 --> 35:55.675
Thank you.

35:57.981 --> 35:59.940
Call me.

36:02.769 --> 36:04.510
CHARLIE: Hey Bettye,
let's grab a drink.

36:04.553 --> 36:07.165
Another time, Charlie,
I got somewhere to be.

36:08.775 --> 36:14.476
♪

36:14.520 --> 36:16.957
Three-to-one odds
they're still setting up.

36:17.000 --> 36:20.526
♪

36:22.615 --> 36:25.183
I feel like I
upset you last night.

36:26.358 --> 36:28.229
I just don't like violence.

36:28.273 --> 36:30.100
Okay.

36:30.144 --> 36:32.581
The guy did
rob you, though.

36:32.625 --> 36:36.194
I know, and I appreciate
you sticking up for me.

36:37.456 --> 36:39.719
But it was just a bag.

36:41.851 --> 36:43.462
I understand.

36:44.332 --> 36:45.899
I'm sorry, Bettye.

36:47.727 --> 36:49.381
It's okay.

36:49.424 --> 36:52.558
[gate screeching]

37:04.613 --> 37:06.615
You didn't get this from me.

37:06.659 --> 37:09.009
Great, thanks.

37:09.531 --> 37:11.229
The hell you
need this for anyway?

37:11.272 --> 37:13.274
You want my
social security number too?

37:13.318 --> 37:14.667
Get the fuck outta here.

37:17.060 --> 37:20.934
♪

37:20.977 --> 37:22.109
Not bad, right?

37:22.152 --> 37:23.197
[chuckles]

37:23.241 --> 37:24.851
♪

37:31.118 --> 37:33.076
Okay.
Come in, everybody in.

37:33.120 --> 37:34.730
Everybody in.[chuckles]

37:34.774 --> 37:36.297
Jesus Christ.

37:36.341 --> 37:38.212
We really need
to upgrade your office, Ruddy.

37:38.256 --> 37:39.692
I'm working on it.

37:39.735 --> 37:42.172
Listen, Charlie saw
the dailies from the Don's of--

37:42.216 --> 37:44.436
Ah, shake it somewhere else,
sweetheart.

37:45.437 --> 37:46.916
Charlie saw the dailies

37:46.960 --> 37:48.396
from the Don's office,
and he hates them.

37:48.440 --> 37:50.442
He said they're too dark,
and he can't hear anything.

37:50.485 --> 37:52.661
Of course they're dark.
I haven't color timed them yet.

37:52.705 --> 37:55.142
His lighting
is gonna be gorgeous, okay?

37:55.185 --> 37:56.709
It's gonna be
like a Caravaggio.

37:56.752 --> 37:58.798
You understand, Evans,
the light and the dark.

37:58.841 --> 38:00.974
Calm down, Francis.
I'm on your side.

38:01.017 --> 38:04.107
Gordy, you color time
those dailies tonight.

38:04.151 --> 38:06.109
Ruddy and I will show Charlie
first thing in the morning.

38:06.153 --> 38:08.111
All right, all right, good.I don't understand.

38:08.155 --> 38:09.939
How the hell did Bluhdorn
even see the dailies again?

38:09.983 --> 38:12.681
I didn't release them.
You didn't release them.

38:13.639 --> 38:16.816
No, but I bet I know who did.

38:16.859 --> 38:18.339
Do you wanna share?

38:18.383 --> 38:20.994
Well, who is it?Yeah, who did?

38:22.038 --> 38:24.127
Hey, hey, Aram.

38:24.171 --> 38:25.781
I told you
nobody sees the dailies

38:25.825 --> 38:26.826
unless I approve it.

38:26.869 --> 38:29.176
Why are you
showing them to Charlie?

38:29.219 --> 38:31.787
If you have a problem,
talk to Jack.

38:31.831 --> 38:33.311
What about it, Jack?

38:33.354 --> 38:35.791
I told Aram
to show Charlie the dailies.

38:35.835 --> 38:37.184
You can't do that.

38:37.227 --> 38:38.838
Mr. Producer,
you seem a little confused.

38:38.881 --> 38:40.796
I'm the vice president
of production at Paramount.

38:40.840 --> 38:42.798
I can do whatever
the fuck I want.

38:48.369 --> 38:51.633
Fucking snake.Hey, Al.

38:51.677 --> 38:54.810
Joe wants to see you.What is this?

38:54.854 --> 38:56.769
The address.

39:00.207 --> 39:02.165
Brooklyn.

39:02.209 --> 39:05.125
[serene guitar music]

39:05.168 --> 39:12.088
♪

39:14.352 --> 39:16.484
You must be Mr. Ruddy.

39:16.528 --> 39:18.399
Please, call me Al.[chuckles]

39:18.443 --> 39:20.836
Welcome to our home.
I'm Joe's wife, Madolina.

39:20.880 --> 39:23.186
So nice to meet you.
Thanks for having me.

39:23.230 --> 39:24.797
Oh, he never
invites anybody over.

39:24.840 --> 39:27.321
I'm so thrilled
to have someone to cook for.

39:27.365 --> 39:29.367
Come on in,
Joe's waiting for you.

39:29.410 --> 39:36.722
♪

39:37.418 --> 39:39.289
COLOMBO:
I hope you came hungry.

39:39.333 --> 39:41.683
There he is.

39:41.727 --> 39:44.033
This is so thoughtful, Joe.Only the best for my friend.

39:44.077 --> 39:45.470
Look at that.Wow.

39:45.513 --> 39:48.037
Huh?
You want something to drink?

39:48.081 --> 39:49.735
[liquid pouring]

39:49.778 --> 39:51.824
Oh, my God.[Madolina chuckles]

39:51.867 --> 39:53.434
That was the best meal
I've ever had.

39:53.478 --> 39:54.870
MADOLINA: Yeah?Yeah.

39:54.914 --> 39:55.958
Aw, That's so kind.

39:56.002 --> 39:57.046
You'll have to roll me
out of here.

39:57.090 --> 39:58.352
[both laugh]

39:58.396 --> 40:00.398
All right. I'll start
the espresso, all right?

40:00.441 --> 40:02.225
Let me take your plate.I can help you.

40:02.269 --> 40:04.010
No, no, no, no, Please.You sure?

40:04.053 --> 40:05.490
Yeah, sit down.Sit down, sit down for a bit.

40:05.533 --> 40:08.188
Thanks.Thank you, doll, thank you.

40:08.231 --> 40:09.450
She's some cook.

40:09.494 --> 40:10.930
She's a good woman.
I'm a lucky man.

40:10.973 --> 40:12.888
I would gain 80 pounds
married to her.

40:12.932 --> 40:15.064
[laughs] Well...

40:15.108 --> 40:16.762
[snorts]

40:19.068 --> 40:20.243
Hey, so...

40:20.287 --> 40:22.681
Lenny was a little
on edge today.

40:22.724 --> 40:24.900
I had to break up a fight
between him and the caterer.

40:24.944 --> 40:27.468
He was saying something
about Joe Gallo.

40:29.514 --> 40:30.863
Lenny's fine.

40:30.906 --> 40:32.604
Ain't nothing
to be concerned about.

40:33.300 --> 40:34.736
Okay.

40:34.780 --> 40:36.738
How about you, though,
everything okay?

40:36.782 --> 40:38.566
Are you worried about me?

40:38.610 --> 40:40.438
[laughs]
Yeah, maybe.

40:40.481 --> 40:42.048
Well, thanks,
I got it covered.

40:42.091 --> 40:43.223
I got it covered.

40:45.225 --> 40:47.662
Well, you see that right there?

40:47.706 --> 40:49.447
This was the first rally.

40:49.490 --> 40:52.232
50,000 people
showed up that day.

40:52.275 --> 40:53.581
That's impressive, Joe.

40:53.625 --> 40:54.800
That ain't nothing.

40:54.843 --> 40:56.932
Tomorrow's supposed
to be a lot more.

40:58.456 --> 40:59.848
RUDDY: Is that your boy?

40:59.892 --> 41:02.111
Yeah.
Yeah, he's a good kid.

41:02.155 --> 41:04.200
He's smart.
He's personable.

41:04.244 --> 41:05.550
I'm gonna get him
into law school,

41:05.593 --> 41:07.203
and then politics.

41:07.247 --> 41:08.466
Politics?

41:08.509 --> 41:10.468
Yeah, I like the sound
of Senator Colombo.

41:10.511 --> 41:13.079
What do you think?That's got a nice ring to it.

41:14.646 --> 41:16.474
So no family business
for him, huh?

41:16.517 --> 41:18.737
No, no, no, no, no.

41:18.780 --> 41:21.130
No, he's not cut out
for this life.

41:21.174 --> 41:24.220
You're probably the only guy
I could admit this to,

41:24.264 --> 41:26.614
but he's soft.

41:26.658 --> 41:28.747
He doesn't have it in him.

41:30.836 --> 41:33.621
You have to learn early in life
if you're the kind of guy

41:33.665 --> 41:36.058
who could hit somebody over
the head with a baseball bat.

41:36.102 --> 41:37.843
You know what I mean?

41:40.541 --> 41:41.934
Yeah, I mean,
if we're being honest,

41:41.977 --> 41:44.414
I don't think
I can do that either.

41:45.198 --> 41:46.895
I got no problem
standing up for myself,

41:46.939 --> 41:49.855
but I don't know
if I could do that.

41:50.508 --> 41:53.032
I think that's why I like you.

41:53.075 --> 41:57.819
[soft music]

41:57.863 --> 41:59.734
You sure you don't want
to take some of this gnocchi?

41:59.778 --> 42:02.694
No, no, I can't.You might get hungry later.

42:02.737 --> 42:04.522
I'm not gonna be hungry
for a year after that.

42:04.565 --> 42:05.914
[chuckles]

42:05.958 --> 42:08.351
We got to do this more often,
you and me.

42:08.395 --> 42:09.962
Say the word,
I'm there, buddy.

42:10.005 --> 42:11.920
You're welcome here anytime,
you know that.

42:11.964 --> 42:12.921
Thank you.

42:12.965 --> 42:14.575
You gonna be
at the rally tomorrow?

42:14.619 --> 42:16.229
Wouldn't miss it
for the world.

42:16.272 --> 42:18.579
But you know I can't get
on stage with you this time.

42:18.623 --> 42:20.929
[laughs]
Fair enough, all right.

42:20.973 --> 42:22.496
I'll save a place
for you up front.

42:22.540 --> 42:24.585
See you, Joe.All right, bye, bye.

42:24.629 --> 42:28.589
♪

42:28.633 --> 42:30.548
These aren't the same.

42:30.591 --> 42:33.333
They are.
They're just color timed.

42:33.376 --> 42:34.682
What does that mean?

42:34.726 --> 42:36.118
It's technical.

42:36.162 --> 42:39.469
It doesn't matter.
Do you see what we see?

42:39.513 --> 42:43.125
[film projector clicking]

42:43.169 --> 42:44.823
Stop.

42:48.130 --> 42:50.393
It's beautiful.

42:50.437 --> 42:52.744
I can't take
my eyes off Brando.

42:52.787 --> 42:54.789
I'm glad you're happy, Charlie.

42:54.833 --> 42:57.226
Now do you trust us?

42:57.270 --> 42:59.620
As far as I can throw you.

43:01.666 --> 43:04.712
Oh, just one more thing.

43:04.756 --> 43:06.888
I need your blessing
on something.

43:06.932 --> 43:08.498
Everyone wants my blessing.

43:08.542 --> 43:10.326
What am I, a fucking priest?

43:13.199 --> 43:15.854
I like how the red
pops on the gold.

43:15.897 --> 43:18.770
That's nice, but I want more.

43:24.123 --> 43:26.125
Like, a lot more.

43:28.344 --> 43:30.738
Yeah, everywhere.

43:30.782 --> 43:34.046
Get Aram and Jack in here
and clear the set.

43:34.089 --> 43:36.439
Okay, everybody,
let's clear the set, please.

43:36.483 --> 43:38.311
It's not fucking real, right?

43:39.617 --> 43:42.358
No, no, of course not.
Come on, Bob.

43:42.402 --> 43:44.709
Well, fuck me.
Props to props.

43:44.752 --> 43:46.624
Hey, hey, whoa! Watch it!

43:46.667 --> 43:48.495
Jesus.Hey, Jack.

43:48.538 --> 43:50.584
Bob.

43:50.628 --> 43:53.413
What's going on?Wow, out of sight.

43:53.456 --> 43:55.720
Wow.

43:55.763 --> 43:58.853
Looks great.You like that?

44:00.333 --> 44:02.770
How can I put this delicately?

44:02.814 --> 44:04.119
You're fired,

44:04.163 --> 44:05.904
you backstabbing son
of a bitch.

44:05.947 --> 44:07.688
Get the hell off my set.Okay, wait a second.

44:07.732 --> 44:09.951
Why don't you get the fuck
out of here too, Jack?

44:11.431 --> 44:14.477
Listen, Mr. Producer,
that's not the way this works.

44:14.521 --> 44:15.696
You can't do that.

44:15.740 --> 44:17.524
But I can.

44:17.567 --> 44:19.526
Excuse me, Al.

44:19.569 --> 44:21.702
Jack...

44:23.095 --> 44:24.357
You're fired.

44:24.400 --> 44:27.316
Now to quote something
I heard mere seconds ago,

44:27.360 --> 44:31.103
"Get the fuck off my set."

44:33.758 --> 44:35.237
Let's go.

44:37.849 --> 44:39.720
This isn't over, Evans.

44:39.764 --> 44:41.461
BOB: Oh, we'll agree
to disagree on that.

44:41.504 --> 44:44.682
Oh, and Jack, you got
a little blood on your collar.

44:44.725 --> 44:46.553
It's right there.

44:46.596 --> 44:48.729
Right there, pal.

44:50.383 --> 44:52.559
Who wants a drink?Ooh.

44:52.602 --> 44:54.343
I can't.
I got somewhere I gotta be.

44:54.387 --> 44:56.476
Aw, raincheck.

44:56.519 --> 44:58.696
Francis?Absolutely.

44:58.739 --> 45:01.176
Ah, Francis, I'm touched.That felt very good.

45:01.220 --> 45:03.352
You know what, man?
That fucking head.

45:03.396 --> 45:04.876
That's something, right?FRANCIS: Yeah.

45:04.919 --> 45:07.008
BOB: That's something.
It could be iconic.

45:07.052 --> 45:08.793
Great work today, Marlon.

45:08.836 --> 45:11.143
Eh, not as great
as the show back there.

45:11.186 --> 45:13.623
You should have
charged admission for it.

45:13.667 --> 45:15.887
You saw all that, huh?

45:15.930 --> 45:18.454
Well, listen, it's not gonna
affect production, trust me.

45:18.498 --> 45:21.588
Oh, no, no, no, I'm not
worried about the production.

45:21.631 --> 45:23.459
As long as Francis
is at the helm,

45:23.503 --> 45:26.071
the rest of it's
just white noise.

45:26.114 --> 45:29.552
I guess that's
the funny thing about power.

45:29.596 --> 45:31.250
What's that?

45:31.293 --> 45:33.556
Well, the ones
who truly have it...

45:33.600 --> 45:35.733
don't gotta talk about it.

45:35.776 --> 45:39.388
[cheers and applause]

45:39.432 --> 45:43.523
ALL: Colombo, Colombo, Colombo,
Colombo, Colombo, Colombo!

45:43.566 --> 45:46.439
[cheers and applause]

45:55.753 --> 45:58.668
[dramatic music]

45:58.712 --> 46:02.324
♪

46:02.368 --> 46:04.718
[crowd screaming]

46:04.762 --> 46:11.899
♪

46:17.818 --> 46:21.082
[siren wailing]

46:21.126 --> 46:26.522
♪

46:26.522 --> 46:31.136
♪

47:44.644 --> 47:47.690
We got a week left in New York,
we'll just keep our heads down

47:47.734 --> 47:48.866
and finish the job,

47:49.127 --> 47:50.563
at least we're done
with the mob.

47:51.781 --> 47:53.174
You know who I am?

47:53.218 --> 47:54.915
I'm Joe Gallo.[GRUNTS]

47:54.959 --> 47:57.396
You can't fuck with this guy,
Al, he's crazy.

47:57.744 --> 47:59.137
What does Gallo want?

47:59.180 --> 48:00.355
AL: The money we have left
for Sicily.

48:00.399 --> 48:02.401
I'll squeeze
that prick producer dry.

48:02.444 --> 48:03.402
BETTYE: Are we safe?

48:05.230 --> 48:07.232
Honestly,
I don't know anymore.

48:07.275 --> 48:07.972
Action!

48:09.321 --> 48:10.322
CHARLES: Something's up
with Evans.

48:10.365 --> 48:10.888
He hasn't been in the office
in days.

48:12.324 --> 48:13.629
The Bob Evans I know
wouldn't let his personal life

48:13.673 --> 48:14.892
compromise this fucking movie!You don't know me!

48:14.935 --> 48:16.110
You don't know me!

48:16.154 --> 48:16.981
BARRY: I'm working on
The Godfather.

48:17.024 --> 48:18.199
Have you read it?Skimmed.

48:18.243 --> 48:19.592
ROBERT: Cut 30 minutes!

48:20.071 --> 48:21.594
They're ruining my picture.

48:21.637 --> 48:22.595
CHARLES: Evans is done.

48:23.944 --> 48:24.640
The guy has given his blood
for your company.

48:24.684 --> 48:25.859
I gave my blood for him.

48:25.903 --> 48:27.034
What the hell are we gonna do?

48:27.078 --> 48:29.341
[EXPLOSION]

48:30.081 --> 48:31.909
JOE GALLO: You know
what is necessary

48:32.735 --> 48:33.998
to get the job done.

48:34.041 --> 48:37.566
This is the start
of a beautiful friendship.

48:37.610 --> 48:38.567
We're gonna keep it...

48:38.611 --> 48:40.569
[CLINKING]

48:40.613 --> 48:49.752
...in the family.

48:49.796 --> 48:51.754
Has anyone seen Pacino?

48:51.798 --> 48:53.365
Yeah, he's right there.

48:53.800 --> 48:55.367
Why is he not in wardrobe?

48:55.410 --> 48:57.630
I don't know, but the kid
better bring his A game today,

48:57.673 --> 48:59.153
otherwise we're fucked.

48:59.197 --> 49:00.938
NIKKI: When Anthony Ippolito
showed up on set

49:00.981 --> 49:03.549
and I heard his voice,
it was uncanny.

49:03.592 --> 49:06.421
It was like being
with the real Al.

49:06.465 --> 49:08.597
Why did we move
the scene up today?

49:08.641 --> 49:12.950
NIKKI: He was not
impervious to being nervous

49:12.993 --> 49:16.083
as he was about to
film the iconic scene

49:16.127 --> 49:19.913
of when Michael Corleone
shoots Sollozzo and McCluskey

49:19.957 --> 49:21.871
in Louis Restaurant.

49:21.915 --> 49:24.352
[GUN POPPING]

49:28.356 --> 49:30.141
They wanna fire me, don't they?

49:31.664 --> 49:33.274
Listen to me, look at me.

49:34.232 --> 49:35.973
We're not gonna let
that happen to you.

49:36.016 --> 49:39.237
Pacino was maybe
about to get fired,

49:39.280 --> 49:42.153
and he's about to do
what now many consider

49:42.196 --> 49:44.982
one of the greatest
scenes captured on film.

49:45.025 --> 49:46.548
It's just incredible.

49:46.592 --> 49:48.028
When you come in here,

49:49.160 --> 49:52.119
I want you to be
extremely nervous.[SIGHS]

49:52.380 --> 49:54.121
That shouldn't be a stretch.

49:54.165 --> 49:55.470
They're talking
about firing him,

49:55.514 --> 49:57.690
the whole production's
gonna unravel,

49:57.733 --> 49:59.126
talking about firing me.

49:59.170 --> 50:01.302
They didn't want
Francis Ford Coppola,

50:01.346 --> 50:03.652
and he was kind of
in director's jail.

50:03.696 --> 50:06.177
And they didn't want Pacino;
nobody knew who he was.

50:06.220 --> 50:08.309
That stuff, to me,
is just amazing.

50:08.353 --> 50:11.530
It's hard to think about them
before they were these legends.

50:11.573 --> 50:15.012
Out there, you're trying
very hard not to show it.

50:15.403 --> 50:17.014
Okay, what scene are we gonna do

50:17.057 --> 50:19.146
to make sure that
everyone loves Pacino?

50:19.190 --> 50:21.714
We do the scene where
Michael has to step up.

50:21.975 --> 50:24.543
This bathroom...

50:25.109 --> 50:26.545
this is the birthplace

50:26.588 --> 50:29.330
of the future
Don Michael Corleone.

50:30.027 --> 50:31.419
DAN:
He has to step up as an actor,

50:31.463 --> 50:33.552
Michael has to step
up in the movie.

50:33.595 --> 50:35.423
So, there's so many
moments like that

50:35.467 --> 50:37.295
where I'm just like, "Ah,
this is just brilliant."

50:37.338 --> 50:39.210
When you put the gun back there,

50:39.558 --> 50:42.039
don't put it there,
put it to the left.

50:43.083 --> 50:45.129
Yeah, and like
six inches higher.

50:45.520 --> 50:47.740
That's perfect.
Do not tell him.

50:47.783 --> 50:50.525
ANTHONY: Dan's so great
and he's so talented,

50:50.569 --> 50:53.659
and what he's doing with
Coppola is so beautiful.

50:53.702 --> 50:55.878
We were both excited
about that bathroom scene.

50:55.922 --> 50:57.271
It's just so cool.

50:59.186 --> 50:59.795
I mean, how many times do you
get to do something like that?

51:01.232 --> 51:02.059
Hey, Charlie, I didn't
know you were coming today.

51:02.102 --> 51:03.756
I was present for
the scene

51:03.799 --> 51:05.453
where Michael shoots McCluskey.

51:05.801 --> 51:08.021
If you imagine, as an actor,
you come to set

51:08.065 --> 51:10.328
and they've
essentially recreated

51:10.371 --> 51:14.419
exactly the cafe where
that scene happened.

51:15.028 --> 51:18.205
[GUNSHOTS][OBJECTS CLATTER, MAN GASPING]

51:18.249 --> 51:20.338
Don't worry, Charlie,
it's not real.

51:21.556 --> 51:23.080
And cut!

51:23.123 --> 51:25.212
BURN: It was also weirdly meta,

51:25.256 --> 51:30.348
because we were watching
Coppola direct Pacino,

51:30.739 --> 51:33.177
and then interacting
with Anthony,

51:33.220 --> 51:36.615
who plays Pacino, as Charlie.

51:37.268 --> 51:39.357
It's sort of a scene within
a scene, within a scene,

51:39.400 --> 51:40.706
but that was a great experience.

51:44.579 --> 51:45.450
Stop.

51:49.149 --> 51:50.672
It's beautiful.
